<A NAME=145East Beach fire>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>East Beach fire</H3><BR>
GOOD EVENING. AND THANKS FOR JOINING US. I'M ALAN MARSDEN.
<P>
20 PEOPLE ARE HOMELESS TONIGHT. AFTER A FIRE RAGES THROUGH A ROOMING HOUSE IN WATSONVILLE.
<P>
THE FIRE STARTED AT ABOUT 7-THIRTY.  IN AN UPSTAIRS BEDROOM OF A HOUSE ON BEACH STREET.
<P>
FIVE DIFFERENT CREWS OF FIREFIGHTERS WERE ABLE TO QUICKLY GET THE BLAZE UNDER CONTROL. 
<P>
BUT NOT BEFORE IT CAUSED MAJOR DAMAGE TO THE UPSTAIRS BEDROOMS AND ATTIC.
<P>
INVESTIGATORS SAY THEY BELIEVE CLOTHES THAT WERE LEFT TOO CLOSE TO A HEATER. ARE WHAT SPARKED THE FIRE.
<P>
THE HOUSE IS NOW UN-LIVEABLE.
<P>
THE RED CROSS IS ON THE SCENE. AND WILL HELP THE VICTIMS FIND A PLACE TO STAY TONIGHT.
<P>

