<A NAME=146highway 17 closed>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>highway 17 closed</H3><BR>
WHAT STARTED AS A SEMI-TRUCK ACCIDENT ON HIGHWAY 17 IN THE SANTA CRUZ MOUNTAINS. HAS TURNED INTO AN DANGEROUS FUEL SPILL. SHUTTING DOWN THE HIGHWAY TONIGHT.
<P>
TRAFFIC WAS SLOWED FOR HOURS AFTER THE ACCIDENT HAPPENED THIS AFTERNOON. THE DRIVER WAS AIRLIFTED TO STANFORD MEDICAL CENTER.
<P>
BUT LATER. WHILE CREWS WERE ATTEMPTING TO CLEAR THE WRECKED FUEL TANKER. THEY APPARENTLY SPRUNG A LEAK.
<P>
NOW MORE THAN ONE-HUNDRED GALLONS OF FUEL HAVE SPILLED ONTO THE ROADWAY. FORCING THE C-H-P AND CAL-TRANS TO SHUT-DOWN THE HIGHWAY. IN BOTH DIRECTIONS.
<P>
OFFICIALS SAY IT WILL BE ANOTHER THREE HOURS AT LEAST. BEFORE HIGHWAY 17 IS RE-OPENED.
<P>

