<A NAME=108SC hypo chase-GUT>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>SC hypo chase-GUT</H3><BR>
JUST BEFORE EIGHT YESTERDAY MORNING, A SHERIFF'S DEPUTY ROAMING THE OCEAN STREET EXTENSION AREA OF SANTA CRUZ DISCOVERED A WOMAN SITTING IN A "CAR THAT WAS SCATTERED WITH HYPODERMIC NEEDLES."
<P>
WHEN HE TRIED TO INVESTIGATE, THE SUSPECTED DRUG ABUSER ALLEGEDLY TRIED TO RUN HIM OVER, THEN ABANDONED HER CAR AND FLED.
<P>
THE BEWILDERED DEPUTY GAVE UP THE SEARCH, BUT CALLED A TOW TRUCK TO IMPOUND THE CAR.
<P>
AND THAT'S WHEN IT HAPPENED.
<P>
THE TOW TRUCK DRIVER DIDN'T NOTICE A HIDDEN NEEDLE NEAR THE PARKING BRAKE. AND NEITHER DID THE DEPUTY, WHO HAD ALREADY CLEARED OUT FIVE SYRINGES FROM THE CAR.
<P>
THE SYRINGE WAS FILLED WITH BLOOD AND WHAT APPEARED TO BE COCAINE.
<P>
THE DRIVER WAS IMMEDIATELY TREATED AT DOMINICAN HOSPITAL. BUT LIKELY WON'T KNOW UNTIL NEXT WEEK WHETHER THE BLOOD CONTAINED ANY DISEASE.
<P>
IN THE MEANTIME, HIS CO-WORKERS SAY, HE'S DISTRAUGHT.
<P>
THE SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT MANAGED TO CATCH THEIR SUSPECT AND HAVE CHARGED CLAIRE DEVELKIS WITH A SERIES OF OFFENSES.
<P>
MEANWHILE, THE TOW TRUCK DRIVER IS CONSIDERING WHETHER TO CHARGE THE *SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT* WITH NEGLIGENCE, IN A LAWSUIT.
<P>
BUT A SHERIFF'S SPOKESPERSON SAYS. ONLY THE SUSPECTED DRUG ABUSER IS TO BLAME.
<P>

