<A NAME=125Acoustic nets>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>Acoustic nets</H3><BR>
A SMALL SOLUTION TO A BIG PROBLEM HAS FISHERMEN AND ENVIRONMENTALISTS SOUDING A VICTORY BELL.
<P>
A SMALL ORANGE ACOUSTIC DEVICE. CALLED THE "PINGER" MAY BRING AN END TO THE UNINTENTIONAL DEATHS OF SEA MAMMELS CAUGHT IN FISHING NETS.
<P>
THE PINGER IS ATTACHED TO THE NETS. THEN SENDS OFF A PINGING SOUND.  THAT SCARES AWAY WHALES, AND OTHER MARINE MAMMALS.
<P>
FOLLOWING A ONE YEAR TEST BY FISHERMEN. THE REMARKABLE DEVISE APPEARS TO BE WORKING.
<P>
BEGINNING THIS MONTH. THE "PINGER" WILL BE REQUIRED BY THE NATIONAL MARINE FISHERIES SERVICE.
<P>

