<A NAME=40Warriors>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>Warriors</H3><BR>
ITS HARD TO IMAGINE, BUT TODAY, THINGS GO FROM BAD TO WORSE FOR LATRELL SPREWELL.
<P>
FOLLOWING LAST NIGHT'S GAME, A LOSS, THE WARRIORS ANNOUNCED THEY WERE TERMINATING THE REMAINING 3-YEARS OF SPREWELL'S CONTRACT FOR VIOLATION OF THE GOOD CONDUCT CLAUSE. THE UNPRESEDENTED MOVE WILL COST SPREWELL ABOUT 24-MILLION DOLLARS.
<P>
THIS MORNING, THE NBA LEVIES ONE OF THE HARSHEST SENTENCES EVER IN PROFESSIONAL SPORTS.
<P>
COMMISSIONER DAVID STERN, IN A STATEMENT RELEASED TODAY, HAS SUSPENDED SPREWELL FOR A FULL YEAR, WITHOUT PAY. FOR WHAT HE CALLS, THE PREMEDITATED ASSUALT ON WARRIORS COACH P.J. CARLESIMO.
<P>
SPREWELL, WHO REPORTEDLY HUNG-UP ON THE NBA OFFICIAL INVESTIGATING THE INCIDENT, IS NOT ELIGIBLE TO RETURN TO THE NBA UNTIL DECEMBER 3RD, 1998.
<P>
THE SHOE COMPANY CONVERSE ALSO DROPPED SPREWELL TODAY AS AN ENDORSER.
<P>
THE 3-TIME ALL-STAR IS SAID TO BE CONSIDERING PLAYING OVERSEES.
<P>
FOR THE WARRIORS, WHO HAVE RECEIVED OVERWHELMING PUBLIC SUPPORT FOR THEIR DECISION, SAID IT WAS THE "RIGHT" THING TO DO.
<P>
THE PLAYERS UNION HAS SAID IT WILL FILE GRIEVANCE ON SPREWELL'S BEHALF AGAINST THE WARRIORS AND THE LEAGUE.
<P>

